@aiwalter I wish I somehow could replicate your conda environment (could you potentially publish it as a docker environment?)

I tried your suggestion as you mentioned. Remarkably, I get an error from installing soft dependencies suggesting that fbprophet does not install. However importing it and printing in a python prompt for the same environment prints 0.7.1.

P.S. Thanks and sorry for my late reply. Working on WSL has so far removed my need for working on windows but once @kanand77 and I resolve #212 I'd love to hop on debugging why this happens (or just get a docker image of your install published! :) )

> conda install -c conda-forge pystan
> conda install -c conda-forge fbprophet

@aiwalter this above code snippet worked for me. I was able to get pytest sktime running successfully after installing pystan and fbprophet w the above method. Thank you!
